.TH "mpt3sas_get_pdev_by_handle" 9 "mpt3sas_get_pdev_by_handle" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
mpt3sas_get_pdev_by_handle \- pcie device search
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct _pcie_device *" mpt3sas_get_pdev_by_handle
.BI "(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc "  ","
.BI "u16 handle "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ioc" 12
per adapter object
.IP "handle" 12
Firmware device handle
.SH "CONTEXT"
This function will acquire ioc->pcie_device_lock and will release
before returning the pcie_device object.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This searches for pcie_device based on handle, then return pcie_device
object.
